{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3699e468-54ee-4b2b-98d8-7283908f710f","content":"The problem is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules defined in files listed *above* them. `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but it depends on `Domain.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_013jC8FYkgouQofrrQmsJ5as","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-5446db18a00e48deaad102be4f1bdc54/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-5446db18a00e48deaad102be4f1bdc54/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"fc1e58f7-69ea-4f40-a61d-4f08307bd837","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file compilation order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files that appear *before* them in the `.fsproj` file. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs (opens BrokenOrder.Domain — but Domain.fs hasn't been compiled yet!)\n2. Domain.fs\n3. Program.fs\n\nThe correct order should be:\n1. Domain.fs (defines types)\n2. Services.fs (uses Domain types)\n3. Program.fs (uses both)","outputTokens":367,"requestId":"441B:3EB10:16FA310:1A0FDEE:69FE8571"},"id":"ca427714-620f-4382-9f23-61e15f4bef3d","timestamp":"2026-05-09T00:53:12.502Z","parentId":"6051cea2-798a-4de4-ba53-e7f02eb54816"}
